trans-unit.source: Provides a standard set of navigation-related commands.
trans-unit.target: Fornece um conjunto padrão de comandos relacionados a navegação.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Windows.Input.NavigationCommands> class exposes a standard set of navigation-related commands, including browser and document navigation.
trans-unit.target: O <xref:System.Windows.Input.NavigationCommands> classe expõe um conjunto padrão de comandos relacionados a navegação, incluindo a navegação do navegador e o documento.

trans-unit.source: For more information on commands and commanding, see [Commanding Overview](~/docs/framework/wpf/advanced/commanding-overview.md).
trans-unit.target: Para obter mais informações sobre comandos e comandos, consulte [visão geral do comando](~/docs/framework/wpf/advanced/commanding-overview.md).

trans-unit.source: Gets the value that represents the <see langword="Browse Back" /> command.
trans-unit.target: Obtém o valor que representa o comando <see langword="Browse Back" />.

trans-unit.source: This command indicates the intention to navigate back to the previous page in the journal.
trans-unit.target: Este comando indica a intenção de navegar de volta para a página anterior no diário.

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame> and <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow> implement support for responding to the <xref:System.Windows.Input.NavigationCommands.BrowseBack%2A>, although you are not required to use it; in many cases the implementation in response to that command is the responsibility of the application writer.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame> e <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow> implementa o suporte de resposta para o <xref:System.Windows.Input.NavigationCommands.BrowseBack%2A>, embora você não deve usá-lo; em muitos casos, a implementação em resposta a esse comando é responsabilidade do gravador de aplicativos.

trans-unit.source: The following example shows how to use <xref:System.Windows.Input.NavigationCommands.BrowseBack%2A> in conjunction with a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>.
trans-unit.target: O exemplo a seguir mostra como usar <xref:System.Windows.Input.NavigationCommands.BrowseBack%2A> em conjunto com um <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame> provides an implementation that responds to the <xref:System.Windows.Input.NavigationCommands.BrowseBack%2A> command by navigating the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame> back, if there are journal entries on the back stack.
trans-unit.target: O <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame> fornece uma implementação que responde ao <xref:System.Windows.Input.NavigationCommands.BrowseBack%2A> comando navegando o <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame> fazer, se houver entradas de diário na pilha voltar.

trans-unit.target: Obtém o valor que representa o comando <see langword="Browse Forward" />.

trans-unit.source: This command indicates the intention to navigate forward the next page in the journal.

trans-unit.target: O exemplo a seguir mostra como usar <xref:System.Windows.Input.NavigationCommands.BrowseForward%2A> em conjunto com um <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>.

trans-unit.target: Como tal, você precisa fornecer uma implementação apropriada, que é mostrada no exemplo.

trans-unit.target: Este comando indica a intenção de navegar no journal.

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame> and <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow> implement support for responding to the <xref:System.Windows.Input.NavigationCommands.NavigateJournal%2A> command, although you are not required to use it; in many cases the implementation in response to that command is the responsibility of the application writer.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame> e <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.NavigationWindow> implementa o suporte de resposta para o <xref:System.Windows.Input.NavigationCommands.NavigateJournal%2A> comando, embora você não deve usá-lo; em muitos casos, a implementação em resposta a esse comando é responsabilidade do gravador de aplicativos.

trans-unit.source: The following example shows how to use <xref:System.Windows.Input.NavigationCommands.NavigateJournal%2A> in conjunction with a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>.
trans-unit.target: O exemplo a seguir mostra como usar <xref:System.Windows.Input.NavigationCommands.NavigateJournal%2A> em conjunto com um <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame> provides an implementation that responds to the <xref:System.Windows.Input.NavigationCommands.NavigateJournal%2A> command by navigating to the specified journal entry on either the forward or back stacks of the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>.
trans-unit.target: O <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame> fornece uma implementação que responde ao <xref:System.Windows.Input.NavigationCommands.NavigateJournal%2A> comando, navegando para a entrada de diário especificado em pilhas para frente ou voltar do <xref:System.Windows.Controls.Frame>.

trans-unit.source: The journal entries are provided by the <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.JournalEntryUnifiedViewConverter> to the top-level `Navigate Journal` <xref:System.Windows.Controls.MenuItem>.
trans-unit.target: As entradas de diário são fornecidas pelo <xref:System.Windows.Navigation.JournalEntryUnifiedViewConverter> ao nível superior `Navigate Journal` <xref:System.Windows.Controls.MenuItem>.

trans-unit.source: Each journal entry is bound to a child <xref:System.Windows.Controls.MenuItem> that uses the <xref:System.Windows.Input.NavigationCommands.NavigateJournal%2A> command.
trans-unit.target: Cada entrada de diário é associada a um filho <xref:System.Windows.Controls.MenuItem> que usa o <xref:System.Windows.Input.NavigationCommands.NavigateJournal%2A> comando.
